entry.database_comments: ANX: N3O7. General Comments: Monoclinic. LPF Collection Code: 1250272. Sample Preparation: STARTING MATERIALS:V2O5,V2O3. Compound Preparation: powder prepared by reaction at 823 K (1);single crystals grown from reaction at 823 K and 200 MPa for 3 d (2). CRUCIBLE: sealed Vycor tube (1), gold tube (2). ATMOSPHERE: vacuum (1). SOLVENT: water (2). Sample powder alternately annealed and ground. Calculated Pattern Original Remarks: LPF Editor Comment: unit for crystal size omitted, assumed to be mm3. LPF Editor Comment: existence of tetragonal V3O7 (published in 1972 by the same author) not mentioned. Temperature Factor: Reported Anisotropic temperature factors (in Beta) were converted to B. Temperature of Data Collection: 293 K. Wyckoff Sequence: f14 e2. Unit Cell Data Source: Powder Diffraction.
